WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

13
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!

14
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind

15
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide

16
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals

17
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real

18
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

19
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

20
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through

21
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it

22
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

23
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

24
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,

25
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?

26
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!

27
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

28
00:01:50.010 --> 00:01:56.260
<b>Captain Kuro</b>

29
00:01:52.550 --> 00:01:56.300
Don't call it an assassination.
That has a bad ring to it, Jango.

30
00:01:56.300 --> 00:01:58.140
Oh, right.

31
00:01:58.140 --> 00:01:59.770
Accident. It'll be an accident.

32
00:02:01.850 --> 00:02:04.350
Hey, what are those
guys talking about?

33
00:02:04.350 --> 00:02:06.110
D-Don't look at me!

34
00:02:06.110 --> 00:02:08.570
That's what I'd like to know!

35
00:02:08.980 --> 00:02:11.530
We can't simply kill her.

36
00:02:11.530 --> 00:02:15.450
Miss Kaya must pass away
due to an unfortunate accident.

37
00:02:15.450 --> 00:02:17.030
You better not mess up!

38
00:02:18.080 --> 00:02:23.960
So basically, on your signal, the men
and I storm the village and kill the girl.

39
00:02:24.460 --> 00:02:27.710
Then you'll get her inheritance.

40
00:02:27.710 --> 00:02:30.590
Imbecile! Use your head!

41
00:02:30.590 --> 00:02:34.130
How could I, an outsider,
inherit Kaya's estate?!

42
00:02:34.130 --> 00:02:36.010
By working hard for it?

43
00:02:36.010 --> 00:02:37.720
Working hard is futile.

44
00:02:38.600 --> 00:02:41.640
Listen, this is the most
important part!

45
00:02:41.640 --> 00:02:45.690
Before killing her, you'll use hypnosis
to make Kaya write her will to say...

46
00:02:46.060 --> 00:02:50.190
"I leave my entire fortune
to my butler, Klahadore!"

47
00:02:52.440 --> 00:02:57.450
Only then will I inherit
her enormous fortune...

48
00:02:58.200 --> 00:03:00.910
in a completely legitimate manner.

49
00:03:01.790 --> 00:03:06.620
I've spent three long years gaining
the trust of everyone around her,

50
00:03:06.620 --> 00:03:10.840
so no one would bat an eye when
she leaves me her inheritance.

51
00:03:11.460 --> 00:03:14.800
Three years as a butler for that, huh?

52
00:03:14.800 --> 00:03:17.390
You sure scared us back then,

53
00:03:17.390 --> 00:03:18.470
Captain Kuro.

54
00:03:19.390 --> 00:03:23.220
Three years ago, you suddenly said
you were giving up life as a pirate.

55
00:03:23.930 --> 00:03:27.190
Just like that, you set up
a subordinate as your double...

56
00:03:27.190 --> 00:03:30.860
and let "Captain Kuro" be
executed for the world to see.

57
00:03:41.450 --> 00:03:45.330
So that was the beginning of this plan.

58
00:03:45.330 --> 00:03:47.370
You truly are Kuro
of a Thousand Plans.

59
00:03:47.370 --> 00:03:49.670
Don't call me that.

60
00:03:49.670 --> 00:03:51.880
I abandoned that name
three years ago.

61
00:03:52.130 --> 00:03:56.630
All I want now is to obtain vast riches
free from government pursuit.

62
00:03:56.630 --> 00:03:59.220
In other words, I'm a pacifist now.

63
00:04:01.050 --> 00:04:03.720
A "pacifist," he says!

64
00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:08.190
What kind of pacifist murders
a rich girl's entire family?

65
00:04:08.190 --> 00:04:09.270
Hold on, now.

66
00:04:09.270 --> 00:04:11.730
The father's death was real.

67
00:04:11.730 --> 00:04:13.610
I hadn't planned on that.

68
00:04:13.860 --> 00:04:14.940
Oh well.

69
00:04:14.940 --> 00:04:16.570
It doesn't matter.

70
00:04:16.570 --> 00:04:19.030
Just give us the signal already.

71
00:04:19.030 --> 00:04:24.080
We've been waiting offshore
for almost a whole week now.

72
00:04:24.660 --> 00:04:27.710
The men are starting to get antsy.

73
00:04:33.880 --> 00:04:35.460
This isn't good!

74
00:04:36.210 --> 00:04:39.090
We overheard something terrible!

75
00:04:40.340 --> 00:04:43.050
Hey, what's going on?
That sounds kind of bad.

76
00:04:43.050 --> 00:04:46.600
Weren't you listening?!
This is seriously bad!

77
00:04:46.600 --> 00:04:47.930
They're the real deal!

78
00:04:48.270 --> 00:04:55.150
Captain Kuro is known as the most
cunning and ruthless pirate of all!

79
00:04:55.980 --> 00:05:00.240
I'd heard the Marines caught
and executed him three years ago...

80
00:05:00.240 --> 00:05:02.660
but Captain Kuro is alive...

81
00:05:02.660 --> 00:05:05.200
as Klahadore, the butler!

82
00:05:05.200 --> 00:05:10.830
He's been after Kaya's fortune
for the past three years!

83
00:05:12.380 --> 00:05:14.500
They're gonna attack the village!

84
00:05:15.040 --> 00:05:16.050
Kaya's in danger, too!

85
00:05:19.420 --> 00:05:20.590
This is bad!

86
00:05:20.590 --> 00:05:22.890
This is seriously bad!

87
00:05:25.680 --> 00:05:28.100
H-Hey, don't stand up!
They'll see you!

88
00:05:28.100 --> 00:05:29.390
Hey, you guys!

89
00:05:29.390 --> 00:05:31.190
Leave that girl alone!

90
00:05:33.230 --> 00:05:34.400
Who's there?!

91
00:05:34.400 --> 00:05:37.320
You idiot! They spotted you!

92
00:05:37.320 --> 00:05:39.360
Quick! Hide before they kill you!

93
00:05:39.740 --> 00:05:40.990
Well...

94
00:05:40.990 --> 00:05:43.740
If it isn't Usopp.

95
00:05:44.990 --> 00:05:46.700
They spotted me, too!

96
00:05:47.330 --> 00:05:50.660
Hear anything... interesting?

97
00:05:50.660 --> 00:05:53.370
N-No! Wh-Whatever do you mean?!

98
00:05:53.370 --> 00:05:56.130
We just got here, so we
couldn't have heard any–

99
00:05:56.130 --> 00:05:57.300
We heard everything!

100
00:05:57.300 --> 00:05:58.340
Hey!

101
00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:07.760
All right, all right...

102
00:06:08.510 --> 00:06:10.270
Hey, blockheads!

103
00:06:10.730 --> 00:06:12.440
Watch this ring closely!

104
00:06:12.730 --> 00:06:14.310
Huh? What's that?

105
00:06:14.310 --> 00:06:17.440
Th-This is bad! It's a throwing
weapon! Dodge it!

106
00:06:18.440 --> 00:06:21.690
On the count of "one, two,
Jango," you'll get very sleepy.

107
00:06:21.690 --> 00:06:23.150
Ready?

108
00:06:23.150 --> 00:06:24.530
One,

109
00:06:23.700 --> 00:06:26.120
Hide! He's gonna kill us!

110
00:06:24.530 --> 00:06:25.570
two...

111
00:06:26.120 --> 00:06:27.070
Jango!

112
00:06:32.200 --> 00:06:33.830
Hey, wake up, Jango!

113
00:06:33.830 --> 00:06:36.040
Have you still not fixed that habit?!

114
00:06:38.250 --> 00:06:40.880
H-Hey, what're you doing?!
You're gonna fall!

115
00:06:44.680 --> 00:06:47.930
Man, head-first, huh?

116
00:06:47.930 --> 00:06:50.560
I didn't mean to kill him,

117
00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:53.180
but there's no way
he survived that fall...

118
00:06:53.560 --> 00:06:54.520
Dammit!

119
00:06:55.770 --> 00:06:57.020
He killed him!

120
00:06:57.020 --> 00:06:58.150
That bastard!

121
00:06:58.150 --> 00:06:59.480
Dammit!

122
00:06:59.940 --> 00:07:01.480
What about the other one?

123
00:07:01.480 --> 00:07:03.240
Shall I take care of him?

124
00:07:03.240 --> 00:07:04.450
No need.

125
00:07:04.820 --> 00:07:07.620
Whatever he does
won't make a difference.

126
00:07:09.580 --> 00:07:11.620
Tomorrow morning, Jango.

127
00:07:11.620 --> 00:07:13.960
Attack the village at daybreak.

128
00:07:13.960 --> 00:07:16.170
Ransack the villagers' homes,

129
00:07:16.170 --> 00:07:20.540
and make certain Miss Kaya's
murder looks like an accident!

130
00:07:21.920 --> 00:07:23.010
Tomorrow!

131
00:07:23.340 --> 00:07:25.760
That's how it is, Usopp.

132
00:07:25.760 --> 00:07:30.510
No matter what you heard,
you can't stop my plan.

133
00:07:30.510 --> 00:07:31.930
Dammit!

134
00:07:35.890 --> 00:07:37.350
You sure about him?

135
00:07:37.350 --> 00:07:40.400
Of course. My plans are flawless.

136
00:07:42.820 --> 00:07:45.360
This is bad! This is really, really bad!

137
00:07:45.860 --> 00:07:48.780
Everyone I grew up with
is going to be killed!

138
00:07:48.780 --> 00:07:50.870
Kaya is going to be killed!

139
00:07:51.240 --> 00:07:54.910
Everyone I love!

140
00:07:57.080 --> 00:07:58.670
Who are you?!

141
00:07:58.670 --> 00:08:00.330
The name's Usopp!

142
00:08:00.330 --> 00:08:02.340
I'm a brave warrior of the sea!

143
00:08:03.420 --> 00:08:05.460
I hear you've been down lately!

144
00:08:05.460 --> 00:08:07.510
I'll cheer you up with a story!

145
00:08:08.010 --> 00:08:09.890
Mind your own business!

146
00:08:09.890 --> 00:08:10.890
Please leave!

147
00:08:10.890 --> 00:08:12.640
I'll call for someone!

148
00:08:16.140 --> 00:08:18.560
And then? What happened after that?!

149
00:08:18.560 --> 00:08:20.310
I fought, of course!

150
00:08:22.230 --> 00:08:26.780
Dammit!

151
00:08:31.240 --> 00:08:32.620
– Captain!
– Captain!

152
00:08:32.620 --> 00:08:35.830
Huh? Wasn't Luffy with him?

153
00:08:38.040 --> 00:08:39.210
– Captain!
– Captain!

154
00:08:40.330 --> 00:08:42.670
Where's Luffy? Didn't you
go to the shore toge...

155
00:08:47.010 --> 00:08:51.340
Is he still mad about
his dad being insulted?

156
00:08:52.680 --> 00:08:54.310
Who knows?

157
00:08:54.560 --> 00:08:56.810
No, that look was different!

158
00:08:56.810 --> 00:08:58.560
Yeah, something must've happened!

159
00:08:58.560 --> 00:09:01.020
What could've freaked
him out like that?

160
00:09:01.850 --> 00:09:04.400
Hey, how do we get to that shore?

161
00:09:04.770 --> 00:09:06.900
Doesn't this smell like trouble?!

162
00:09:06.900 --> 00:09:09.200
Yeah! Something
went down at the shore!

163
00:09:09.200 --> 00:09:11.360
This is a job for the Usopp Pirates!

164
00:09:11.610 --> 00:09:14.240
Alright, already!
How do we get there?!

165
00:09:19.080 --> 00:09:22.250
Terrible news, everyone!

166
00:09:22.250 --> 00:09:26.710
The pirates are coming!

167
00:09:30.130 --> 00:09:33.930
Pirates are going to raid
this village tomorrow morning!

168
00:09:33.930 --> 00:09:35.760
Run away, everyone!

169
00:09:53.490 --> 00:09:54.700
Alright, Usopp!

170
00:09:54.700 --> 00:09:56.910
Enough is enough!

171
00:09:56.910 --> 00:10:00.120
We'll shut you up for good!

172
00:10:00.120 --> 00:10:02.620
N-No, it's not like that!

173
00:10:02.620 --> 00:10:03.960
It's the truth this time!

174
00:10:04.210 --> 00:10:07.290
Shut up! All you ever do
is spout huge lies!

175
00:10:07.290 --> 00:10:11.470
If you were as honest as Klahadore,
maybe we'd actually believe you!

176
00:10:11.510 --> 00:10:14.390
Whatever he does
won't make a difference.

177
00:10:14.390 --> 00:10:15.970
Tomorrow morning, Jango.

178
00:10:15.970 --> 00:10:18.220
Attack the village at daybreak.

179
00:10:18.970 --> 00:10:20.350
Dammit!

180
00:10:20.350 --> 00:10:25.520
So he let me go... because
he knew no one would believe me?!

181
00:10:31.860 --> 00:10:34.110
Are these to your liking?

182
00:10:35.030 --> 00:10:38.160
I picked up the glasses
you custom-ordered...

183
00:10:38.490 --> 00:10:40.700
from the next town over.

184
00:10:40.700 --> 00:10:42.580
Yes, they're perfect!

185
00:10:43.580 --> 00:10:47.130
I'm sorry for asking you
to go all the way there.

186
00:10:53.920 --> 00:10:55.300
It's a present, isn't it?

187
00:10:55.300 --> 00:10:56.550
Yes.

188
00:10:56.550 --> 00:11:01.060
Tomorrow will be three years since
Klahadore came to this mansion.

189
00:11:01.060 --> 00:11:03.310
He's always taken
good care of me, so...

190
00:11:03.850 --> 00:11:06.480
Klahadore will be delighted!

191
00:11:06.480 --> 00:11:07.270
He will!

192
00:11:10.020 --> 00:11:12.530
Everyone, please listen to me!

193
00:11:12.900 --> 00:11:15.610
Pirates really will attack
tomorrow morning!

194
00:11:15.990 --> 00:11:20.990
If we believed every one of your tall tales,
we'd have fled hundreds of times by now!

195
00:11:20.990 --> 00:11:23.580
Please believe me!
You gotta get out of here!

196
00:11:23.580 --> 00:11:26.710
They really are going to kill everyone!

197
00:11:26.710 --> 00:11:29.500
I swear it's the truth this time!

198
00:11:29.500 --> 00:11:32.210
And we're gonna get you this time!

199
00:11:35.630 --> 00:11:37.760
Dammit!

200
00:11:37.760 --> 00:11:40.050
Get him! Don't let him escape!

201
00:11:48.060 --> 00:11:51.110
Thank you for coming, men.

202
00:11:51.110 --> 00:11:53.070
It's truly been a long three years.

203
00:11:53.650 --> 00:11:56.320
Once this plan succeeds,

204
00:11:56.320 --> 00:12:00.530
I intend to give you all
a fair share of the plunder.

205
00:12:01.490 --> 00:12:05.580
At dawn tomorrow, ransack the village
to your hearts' content!

206
00:12:13.050 --> 00:12:15.510
– What?! They're going to kill Miss Kaya?!
– What?! They're going to kill Miss Kaya?!

207
00:12:15.510 --> 00:12:18.720
– Are they really going to attack the village?!
– Are they really going to attack the village?!

208
00:12:19.470 --> 00:12:20.340
Yeah.

209
00:12:20.340 --> 00:12:22.680
That's what they said.
No doubt about it.

210
00:12:26.850 --> 00:12:29.730
So what were you doing
sleeping down here?

211
00:12:30.190 --> 00:12:31.400
That's the thing!

212
00:12:31.400 --> 00:12:34.230
I thought I was on top of the cliff...

213
00:12:34.730 --> 00:12:37.320
So how'd I get down here?

214
00:12:35.190 --> 00:12:37.490
We were right! Klahadore's a bad guy!

215
00:12:37.490 --> 00:12:39.070
No wonder he seems so creepy!

216
00:12:39.070 --> 00:12:42.990
So that's why our captain ran to
the village with that intense look!

217
00:12:42.990 --> 00:12:44.290
That's great, then!

218
00:12:44.290 --> 00:12:47.250
They have time to escape now
that they've been warned.

219
00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:48.790
Talk about dumb bad guys!

220
00:12:48.790 --> 00:12:51.710
Yeah, that's right!
We gotta run away, too!

221
00:12:51.710 --> 00:12:53.540
Yeah, we better grab our valuables...

222
00:12:53.540 --> 00:12:54.500
– ...and hurry!
– ...and hurry!

223
00:12:58.220 --> 00:12:58.880
Oh no!

224
00:12:58.880 --> 00:12:59.970
What?

225
00:13:00.470 --> 00:13:03.850
We need to stock up on food
before the meat shop guy runs away!

226
00:13:04.970 --> 00:13:07.180
That's not the problem here.

227
00:13:24.070 --> 00:13:25.240
Usopp!

228
00:13:31.670 --> 00:13:32.830
Thank goodness!

229
00:13:32.830 --> 00:13:35.340
I thought you might
never come back...

230
00:13:36.500 --> 00:13:38.340
You gotta run, Kaya!

231
00:13:38.340 --> 00:13:39.550
They're gonna kill you!

232
00:13:39.800 --> 00:13:40.590
Um...

233
00:13:41.300 --> 00:13:42.630
What do you mean?

234
00:13:42.630 --> 00:13:44.550
You've been tricked!

235
00:13:44.550 --> 00:13:46.720
Your butler is actually a pirate!

236
00:13:47.810 --> 00:13:49.310
Hold on...

237
00:13:50.480 --> 00:13:52.270
What kind of joke is this?

238
00:13:53.560 --> 00:13:54.980
It's no joke!

239
00:13:54.980 --> 00:13:57.150
I heard it with my own ears!

240
00:13:57.480 --> 00:13:58.730
Klahadore's a pirate...

241
00:13:58.730 --> 00:14:02.530
who weaseled his way into
this mansion to steal your fortune!

242
00:14:02.530 --> 00:14:07.120
He's been pretending to be a butler for
three whole years just so he could rob you!

243
00:14:07.910 --> 00:14:11.160
What are you talking about, Usopp?

244
00:14:11.660 --> 00:14:16.130
He said his crew's gonna storm in
and kill you at dawn tomorrow!

245
00:14:20.460 --> 00:14:25.050
This guy's as bad as they come!
You gotta escape, quick!

246
00:14:26.640 --> 00:14:29.390
I admit, he did go too far earlier.

247
00:14:30.020 --> 00:14:32.020
But lying like this...

248
00:14:32.980 --> 00:14:34.690
It's not like you, Usopp!

249
00:14:36.310 --> 00:14:39.110
No, it's not a lie...

250
00:14:42.070 --> 00:14:43.110
I...

251
00:14:44.150 --> 00:14:45.950
I loved them.

252
00:14:48.370 --> 00:14:51.750
I loved the lies you told...

253
00:14:52.120 --> 00:14:54.790
Yet, why are you saying this?

254
00:14:56.790 --> 00:15:01.210
It's not like that! I'm not trying
to get back at Klahadore...

255
00:15:01.590 --> 00:15:04.430
So why say it...?

256
00:15:04.430 --> 00:15:06.390
Kaya... I...

257
00:15:08.180 --> 00:15:10.510
Is something the matter, Miss?!

258
00:15:15.810 --> 00:15:17.350
You gotta escape, Kaya!

259
00:15:17.940 --> 00:15:20.270
Unhand her this instant!

260
00:15:21.730 --> 00:15:23.650
Just trust me!

261
00:15:23.650 --> 00:15:25.650
You gotta get out of this village...

262
00:15:25.650 --> 00:15:28.200
before that butler gets back!

263
00:15:40.420 --> 00:15:41.590
Stop!

264
00:15:44.720 --> 00:15:45.260
Come on!

265
00:15:50.930 --> 00:15:53.220
This will all make sense tomorrow!

266
00:15:53.220 --> 00:15:54.980
But you gotta escape for now!

267
00:15:54.980 --> 00:15:56.440
Please, listen to me!

268
00:16:05.240 --> 00:16:06.900
You're pathetic.

269
00:16:18.370 --> 00:16:20.290
Get away from her!

270
00:16:23.670 --> 00:16:24.380
No!

271
00:16:37.980 --> 00:16:39.980
Please, catch him!

272
00:16:39.980 --> 00:16:42.190
He roughed up the lady of the house!

273
00:16:42.520 --> 00:16:43.480
How horrible!

274
00:16:43.480 --> 00:16:44.820
How could he?!

275
00:16:49.570 --> 00:16:50.660
Why...

276
00:16:51.820 --> 00:16:53.830
Why won't anyone believe me?

277
00:16:57.250 --> 00:16:58.870
There he is!

278
00:16:58.870 --> 00:17:00.420
Get him!

279
00:17:06.380 --> 00:17:08.630
Usopp...

280
00:17:09.380 --> 00:17:12.430
Please maintain
your composure, miss!

281
00:17:15.890 --> 00:17:18.140
Tomorrow morning, Jango.

282
00:17:18.140 --> 00:17:20.890
Attack the village at daybreak!

283
00:17:28.440 --> 00:17:30.450
– Captain!
– Captain!

284
00:17:33.030 --> 00:17:34.780
Hey, guys!

285
00:17:35.410 --> 00:17:36.450
Hey!

286
00:17:38.160 --> 00:17:40.120
Y-You're alive?!

287
00:17:40.120 --> 00:17:41.500
Alive?

288
00:17:41.500 --> 00:17:43.670
Yeah, I just woke up!

289
00:17:43.670 --> 00:17:45.460
He was asleep this whole time!

290
00:17:45.460 --> 00:17:46.800
Anyway, Captain!

291
00:17:46.800 --> 00:17:48.670
We heard everything!

292
00:17:48.670 --> 00:17:52.050
Let's hurry and tell everyone
about the pirates!

293
00:17:52.050 --> 00:17:54.010
Tell everyone?

294
00:17:57.010 --> 00:17:58.470
You're pathetic.

295
00:18:00.930 --> 00:18:03.350
Shut up! All you ever do
is spout huge lies!

296
00:18:12.610 --> 00:18:15.070
I'm lying as usual, obviously!

297
00:18:15.070 --> 00:18:17.080
That damn butler pissed me off,

298
00:18:17.080 --> 00:18:20.040
so I made up a lie about
him being a pirate!

299
00:18:21.830 --> 00:18:23.330
Oh, I see!

300
00:18:23.330 --> 00:18:26.290
So the straw hat guy is in on it, too!

301
00:18:30.760 --> 00:18:32.720
Hey, what's wrong?

302
00:18:32.720 --> 00:18:33.470
I...

303
00:18:33.880 --> 00:18:35.840
I can't believe you'd do that, Captain.

304
00:18:35.840 --> 00:18:36.470
Me neither!

305
00:18:36.470 --> 00:18:37.510
Same here!

306
00:18:37.510 --> 00:18:39.470
Even if that butler is a jerk,

307
00:18:39.470 --> 00:18:44.140
I never thought you would lie
just to hurt someone!

308
00:18:44.140 --> 00:18:47.440
We really respected you, too!

309
00:18:47.440 --> 00:18:48.320
Let's go home!

310
00:18:48.320 --> 00:18:50.030
Yeah, it's suppertime!

311
00:18:50.030 --> 00:18:51.570
Wonder what we're having...

312
00:18:57.370 --> 00:18:59.910
Why did you tell them that?

313
00:18:59.910 --> 00:19:02.080
Because I'm a liar.

314
00:19:02.080 --> 00:19:05.540
They were never going to
believe me from the start.

315
00:19:05.540 --> 00:19:06.830
I was too optimistic.

316
00:19:07.960 --> 00:19:10.800
Even so, the truth is the truth.

317
00:19:11.300 --> 00:19:14.340
Pirates really are going
to come, aren't they?

318
00:19:14.340 --> 00:19:16.890
Yeah, they're definitely
gonna show up.

319
00:19:16.890 --> 00:19:19.390
But everyone thinks it's a lie.

320
00:19:19.390 --> 00:19:23.520
They think tomorrow will be
just another normal, peaceful day...

321
00:19:25.810 --> 00:19:26.940
That's why...

322
00:19:26.940 --> 00:19:30.860
I'm gonna stop the pirates at the beach
tomorrow and make sure it stays a lie!

323
00:19:30.860 --> 00:19:34.820
That's the only thing that
makes sense for a liar like me!

324
00:19:36.450 --> 00:19:38.990
Even if I get shot in the arm...

325
00:19:39.530 --> 00:19:42.040
or driven off with brooms...

326
00:19:42.040 --> 00:19:44.330
this is my home!

327
00:19:44.330 --> 00:19:46.710
I love this village!

328
00:19:48.040 --> 00:19:50.670
I want to protect everyone!

329
00:19:51.630 --> 00:19:53.260
You're one hell of a good guy,

330
00:19:53.260 --> 00:19:56.130
pushing away your crew
and going into battle alone.

331
00:19:56.130 --> 00:19:59.640
Just so you know, I call dibs
on all the pirates' treasure!

332
00:19:59.640 --> 00:20:01.600
Alright! We'll help you out!

333
00:20:02.100 --> 00:20:03.100
You guys...

334
00:20:03.100 --> 00:20:05.350
are going to fight with me?!

335
00:20:05.350 --> 00:20:06.560
Why?

336
00:20:06.560 --> 00:20:09.860
Well, you're way outnumbered, right?

337
00:20:09.860 --> 00:20:12.070
"Scared" is written all over your face.

338
00:20:12.070 --> 00:20:13.900
M-Me, scared?!

339
00:20:13.900 --> 00:20:17.070
I'm perfectly fine against
lots of bad guys or whatever!

340
00:20:17.070 --> 00:20:22.240
After all, I'm Captain Usopp,
brave warrior of the sea!

341
00:20:24.660 --> 00:20:25.750
Dammit! Dammit!

342
00:20:25.750 --> 00:20:27.500
What're you looking at?!

343
00:20:27.500 --> 00:20:29.750
We're dealing with Klahadore's crew!

344
00:20:29.750 --> 00:20:31.210
Of course I'm scared!

345
00:20:31.210 --> 00:20:32.710
What's wrong with that?!

346
00:20:32.710 --> 00:20:34.710
I don't want your pity!

347
00:20:34.710 --> 00:20:37.170
Stop laughing and leave! Leave!

348
00:20:37.670 --> 00:20:39.180
We aren't laughing!

349
00:20:39.180 --> 00:20:42.140
It's commendable.
That's why we want to help you.

350
00:20:43.140 --> 00:20:46.100
As if we'd risk our lives out of pity!

351
00:20:51.350 --> 00:20:53.110
Oh...

352
00:20:53.110 --> 00:20:55.030
You guys...

353
00:21:08.210 --> 00:21:15.070
As a kid, I had a dream of a dazzling treasure

354
00:21:15.270 --> 00:21:22.090
I had a map in my head that I knew would lead me

355
00:21:22.340 --> 00:21:29.190
Charted a course all on my own, so nobody would beat me

356
00:21:29.310 --> 00:21:36.450
The promised land was in my hand, drew a line in the sand

357
00:21:39.150 --> 00:21:41.830
Look where I am

358
00:21:44.060 --> 00:21:50.240
My one ambition's slipping right through my hands

359
00:21:50.580 --> 00:21:57.510
But if the world ever changes I'll call out your name

360
00:21:57.670 --> 00:22:04.590
We could return to a time when our lives were still the same

361
00:22:04.720 --> 00:22:11.720
Take me to the place where memories remain

362
00:22:11.820 --> 00:22:17.590
Please don't ever let them fade
